<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-08"><hi rend="italic">January 8,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. O’Brien states that he has learned indirectly from the prime minister
                            that Japan will decline suggestion of December 18. He adds that a formal
                            reply is being considered, but is not yet ready.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>